JOHANNESBURG - The accusations that MTN is supporting terrorism don't surprise one researcher. A US court has been told the cellular network operator and other large corporates made payments to the Taliban, to protect their businesses in Afghanistan. READ: MTN accused of supporting terrorism The US regards the Taliban as a terrorist organisation.
Ebrahim Deen, an Afro-Middle East Centre researcher said it is an unfortunate thing. "If you look at the report, they are accusing the US defence companies as well of flouting US regulations. READ: MTN denies terror claims "It's something that has happened. It happens in all war zones. "It happened in apartheid SA where you had these British companies supporting apartheid government."